    "treatments": "Treatment for Sinus Node Dysfunction often focuses on managing symptoms and may vary based on the severity of the condition. In mild cases, a doctor may recommend lifestyle modifications such as avoiding triggers and managing stress. For those experiencing significant symptoms or complications, a pacemaker may be implanted to regulate the heart's rhythm and ensure it beats at an appropriate rate. Regular follow-up with a cardiologist is important to monitor the patient's condition and make any necessary adjustments to treatment."
